globe4r 0.0.1
  • Reference

    Interactive globes for R via globe.gl Create 3D globes with points, bar, choropleth (polygons), arcs, and labels.


    Installation

    You can install the globe4r from Github:

    # install.packages("remotes")
remotes::install_github("JohnCoene/globe4r")

    Example

    This is a basic example which shows you how to solve a common problem:

    library(globe4r)

create_globe(width = "100%") %>% # initialise
  globe_img_url() %>% # add image background
  globe_pov( # position camera
    lat = -21, 
    lon = 160,
    ms = 5000
  ) %>% 
  globe_points( # add points
    data = quakes,
    lat = lat,
    lon = long,
    color = mag,
    altitude = mag
  ) %>% 
  scale_points_color() %>% 
  scale_points_altitude(0, .25)
